==English==

===Adjective===
'''token'''

# Done as an [[indication]] or a [[pledge]]
# [[perfunctory]], [[minimal]] or [[merely]] [[symbolic]]

===Noun===
'''token''' (plural: [[tokens]])

#Something serving as an [[expression]] of something else
#Something that [[signify|signifies]] the [[authority]] or [[identity]] of something
#One who [[represent]]s a [[group]]
#A [[keepsake]] or [[souvenir]]
#A piece of [[stamp]]ed [[metal]] used as a [[substitute]] for [[money]]
# {{computing}} An [[atomic]] piece of data (esp. the text of a computer program) for which a meaning may be inferred during parsing. Also called a [[symbol]] or [[lexeme]].
#In computer security, a token is a small physical device for storing cryptographic keys.

